'''Roboto'''是为[[Android|Android]]操作系统设计的一个[[无衬线字体|无衬线字体]]家族<ref name="Sandwich">{{cite web |url=http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/10/android-ice-cream-sandwich-3/ |title=Google's New Font |author= |date=October 19, 2011 |work=Wired |publisher=Wired |accessdate=November 4, 2011 |archive-date=2014-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140206120233/http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/10/android-ice-cream-sandwich-3 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[Google|Google]]描述该字型为“现代的、但平易近人”和“有感情”的<ref name="ICE">{{cite web |title = New Design Philosophy of Ice Cream Sandwich |url = http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/18/roboto-and-the-new-design-philosophy-of-android-4-0-ice-cream-s/ |work = Engadget |publisher = Engadget |accessdate = November 4, 2011 |archive-date = 2016-05-30 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160530231540/http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/18/roboto-and-the-new-design-philosophy-of-android-4-0-ice-cream-s/ |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Cream">{{cite web
|title = Design of Roboto
|url = http://news.in.msn.com/technology/article.aspx?cp-documentid=5526341
|work = MSN
|publisher = MSN
|accessdate = November 4, 2011
|archive-url = https://archive.today/20121209084519/http://news.in.msn.com/technology/article.aspx?cp-documentid=5526341
|archive-date = 2012-12-09
|dead-url = yes
}}</ref>。该字型在[[Apache许可证|Apache许可证]]下授权使用<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fontsquirrel.com/license/roboto|title=Roboto license|accessdate=2012-01-16|archive-date=2016-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606125717/https://www.fontsquirrel.com/license/roboto|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。整个字型家族在2012年1月12日在新推出的Android设计网站「Android Design」上正式提出以供免费下载<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://developer.android.com/design/style/typography.html |title=Android Design |accessdate=2012-01-16 |archive-date=2012-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114235709/http://developer.android.com/design/style/typography.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这个字型家族包含Thin、Light、Regular、Medium、Bold、Black六种粗细及相配的斜体。此外还包含Condensed样式的Light、Regular和Bold三种粗细及相配的斜体。

